# Neural Net Neutrality - Environment Variables

# ============================================================================
# DATABASE CONNECTION (Required for Voting)
# ============================================================================
# Get this from Supabase: https://supabase.com
# 1. Create a Supabase project (free tier available)
# 2. Go to Settings → Database → Connection info
# 3. Copy the PostgreSQL connection string (Psycopg2 tab)
# Format: postgresql://postgres:PASSWORD@HOST:5432/postgres
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:YOUR_PASSWORD@YOUR_HOST:5432/postgres

# ============================================================================
# LLM API KEYS (Optional - for testing specific providers)
# ============================================================================
# If not set, the system will use API keys from requests or environment

# OpenAI (for GPT-4o, GPT-4o Mini, GPT-3.5 Turbo models)
# Get from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# Anthropic (for Claude 3 Haiku/Sonnet/Opus models)
# Get from: https://console.anthropic.com/
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# Google (for Gemini 1.5 Pro, 2.0 Flash models)
# Get from: https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
GOOGLE_API_KEY=AIzaSy...

# ============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT
# ============================================================================
# For local development: Copy this to .env and fill in your values
# For Render production: Add these variables in Render dashboard → Environment
#
# IMPORTANT SECURITY:
# - NEVER commit .env to git (it's in .gitignore)
# - NEVER share DATABASE_URL or API keys
# - Each developer should have their own .env file
# - For production, use Render environment variables
